---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Three founders. 34 years combined experience. No juniors. You always talk to the people who built the system."
>
  <Section class="pt-28 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="mb-6">You always talk to the people who built the system.</h1>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-xl leading-relaxed">
        WKTW is three founders with 45 years of combined experience in digital growth,
        technical infrastructure, and content strategy &mdash; split across three
        non-overlapping registers, not three slightly different versions of the same
        r&eacute;sum&eacute;. No juniors. No account managers. The people who built
        the diagnostic tools are the people you work with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Team -->
  <Section elevated>
    <h2 class="mb-4">The team</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-10 max-w-3xl">
      Each pillar of The Get Right is owned by a founder whose career is built on it.
      Category authority, function-head operating depth, and engineering rigor &mdash;
      three credibility surfaces, zero overlap.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div id="jon-lister" class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-xl p-8 scroll-mt-24">
        <img
          src="/team/jon-lister.webp"
          alt="Jon Lister"
          width="112"
          height="112"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full object-cover border border-border-subtle mb-6"
        />
        <h3 class="text-xl mb-1">Jon Lister</h3>
        <p class="text-accent text-sm font-mono mb-1">Category authority</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text text-sm font-mono mb-3">23 years &middot; VP, SEO &middot; Horizon Media</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">
          Forbes-featured on Generative Engine Optimization. Public voice for
          one of the most aggressive AI-search positioning bets in the agency
          world. Owns the Content Authority Audit &mdash; the "Search Intelligence"
          framing on which Canary is built is Jon's published worldview.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div id="jason-bauman" class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-xl p-8 scroll-mt-24">
        <img
          src="/team/jason-bauman.webp"
          alt="Jason Bauman"
          width="112"
          height="112"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full object-cover border border-border-subtle mb-6"
        />
        <h3 class="text-xl mb-1">Jason Bauman</h3>
        <p class="text-accent text-sm font-mono mb-1">Function-head operating depth</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text text-sm font-mono mb-3">12 years &middot; Director, Technical Strategy &middot; Publicis Health Media</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">
          Director-tier function leadership at Publicis Groupe's market-leading
          health agency &mdash; the kind of seat that ships strategy under real
          regulatory and stakeholder pressure. Owns the synthesis: the part where
          three audits become one prioritized roadmap your team can actually execute.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div id="brandon-griner" class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-xl p-8 scroll-mt-24">
        <img
          src="/team/brandon-griner.webp"
          alt="Brandon Griner"
          width="112"
          height="112"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full object-cover border border-border-subtle mb-6"
        />
        <h3 class="text-xl mb-1">Brandon Griner</h3>
        <p class="text-accent text-sm font-mono mb-1">Engineering rigor</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text text-sm font-mono mb-3">10 years &middot; SEO Technical Supervisor &middot; Publicis Health Media</p>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">
          BS in Computer Science, MA in Data Science. Career arc from SEO Specialist
          through Data Architect before PHM. Not a marketer who learned data &mdash;
          a data engineer who happens to work in SEO. Built the engineering layer
          that lets Muttr, Canary, and Delphi do in days what agencies do in weeks.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-6">Why we built our own tools</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        We spent years running audits with off-the-shelf tools. They all had the same
        problem: shallow findings, generic recommendations, and zero connection to
        actual revenue impact. The output was technically correct and practically useless.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        So we built what we wished existed. Muttr does deep structural analysis that
        ties every finding to business KPIs. Canary maps content authority at the topic
        level, not the keyword level. Delphi verifies that your measurement foundation
        is solid before you try to build on it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        The tools aren't the product. <span class="text-primary-text">The insight is the product.</span>
        The tools just make sure the insight is grounded in evidence, not opinion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <Section elevated>
    <h2 class="mb-8">How we work</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-3xl">
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-2">Project-first, always</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">We don't sell retainers on day one. We sell a 90-day diagnostic sprint. Continued engagement is earned by proving value, not by contract lock-in.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-2">Backlogs, not reports</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">Every deliverable is designed to be actionable. Sprint-ready tickets, not executive summaries. Your team ships fixes, not reads recommendations.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-2">Revenue-tied everything</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">Every finding is connected to revenue impact. Not "this is a best practice" but "this is costing you approximately $X per month."</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-2">We practice what we preach</h4>
        <p class="text-secondary-text">We run our own tools on our own site and publish the results. Same standards, full transparency.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4">Ready to talk?</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-8">
        No pitch deck. No discovery call script. Just a conversation with someone
        who's been doing this for over a decade.
      </p>
      <Button href="/contact">Talk to a Founder</Button>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Structured Data: Person schemas for the founder triangle -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@graph": [
      {
        "@type": "Person",
        "@id": "https://weknowthewhy.com/about#jon-lister",
        "name": "Jon Lister",
        "givenName": "Jonathan",
        "familyName": "Lister",
        "jobTitle": "Cofounder, WKTW",
        "description": "Cofounder of We Know The Why. VP, SEO at Horizon Media. Forbes-featured on Generative Engine Optimization. Public voice for the 'Search Intelligence' framing of AI-era search. Owns the Content Authority Audit pillar.",
        "url": "https://weknowthewhy.com/about#jon-lister",
        "image": "https://weknowthewhy.com/team/jon-lister.webp",
        "knowsAbout": [
          "Search Engine Optimization",
